Usage:
    python3 %progName% path_to_image_folder [general_options]... [-f|--file filename...]
    python3 %progName% -h|--help

Options:
  General options:
    -w, --width nrows                       number of images per row in the final grid (10 by default)
    -s, --sort number|date                  sort the images in the grid either by the number in their filename or by the creation date of the file (number by default)
    -c, --center top|bottom|both            if there is any incomplete row, centers it in the chosen location(s) (not centered by default)

  Other options:
    -f, --files filename...                 files to be used (overrides -s and default file seeking)
    -h, --help                              prints this message
